Author: Scott#9506
Content: Id like to see ravencoin RVN easier to use on Barterdex. There are a lot of miners out there and the only one main buggy exchange.  It seems like its a real pain to get it to work on Barterdex and I have not figured it out yet.

Author: cipi#4502
Content:
```git clone https://github.com/RavenProject/Ravencoin
cd Ravencoin
./autogen.sh
./configure --with-incompatible-bdb --with-gui=no --disable-tests --disable-bench --without-miniupnpc --disable-zmq
make -j4
sudo make install
sudo strip /usr/local/bin/raven*
mkdir ~/.raven
echo "server=1" >> ~/.raven/raven.conf
echo "txindex=1" >> ~/.raven/raven.conf
echo "listen=0" >> ~/.raven/raven.conf
echo "rpcuser=barterrvn" >> ~/.raven/raven.conf
echo "rpcpassword=`head -c 32 /dev/urandom | base64`" >> ~/.raven/raven.conf
chmod 0600 ~/.raven/raven.conf
ravend -daemon
raven-cli setgenerate false```

Author: cipi#4502
Content: cut&paste that in a shell, start BarterDEX, done
